Commentary Text: SN Thakur to Buttler, out Caught by Dwayne Bravo!! Rajasthan Royals lose their best batter and are in deep trouble. A fuller-than-a-good-length ball on the stumps and Buttler wanted to bash it over mid-on. The ball might have held up into the wicket and that robbed the batter's timing. The bat turned at the point of impact and Buttler ended up slicing it over mid-off. Bravo takes a couple of steps backwards and snaffles it with ease. Buttler c Dwayne Bravo b SN Thakur 6(7) [4s-1]
team_a_11: Chennai Super Kings (Playing XI): Shane Watson, Ambati Rayudu, Suresh Raina, Kedar Jadhav, MS Dhoni(w/c), Dwayne Bravo, Ravindra Jadeja, Mitchell Santner, Deepak Chahar, Shardul Thakur, Imran Tahir

Commentary Text: Chahar to Samson, out Caught by Raina!! The centurion in the previous game is gone! A 134.1kph fullish ball outside off and Samson threw his bat at it. The bottom hand comes off the handle and hence the miscue. Raina takes a sharp catch bending forward, but Samson stands his ground. The on-field umpires send it upstairs with OUT being the soft decision. An easy one for the TV umpire as Raina had both his palms underneath the ball. Samson c Raina b Chahar 8(10) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahar to Rahane, out Caught by Jadeja!! Ideal start for the hosts. A corker from Jaddu at backward point. Another outswinger and Rahane drives with hard hands. Only gets an outside edge that dips as it approached the backward point fielder. Don't think many would have taken it. But, Jadeja is one of the best fielders in world cricket. He swoops forward and takes a diving catch inches above the ground. Rahane asked the fielder and decided to walk off. But, the umpires wanted to be 100% sure and hence went upstairs. Legal ball and a clean catch. A 2-ball duck for the Rajasthan skipper. Rahane c Jadeja b Chahar 0(2)
